President Obama spoke with Aung San Suu Kyi of Burma to discuss the progress of Burma's political and economic reforms and the need for a fair and inclusive process for the upcoming elections in 2015. They also discussed ways in which the United States can support efforts to promote tolerance, diversity, and inclusivity in Burma's political environment. President Obama expressed his appreciation for Aung San Suu Kyi's work in promoting democracy and reiterated the United States' commitment to helping Burma become a more free, open, and prosperous nation.